7 D. 1. The Director of Service Oklahoma is hereby authorized to
8 adopt rules as may be necessary to enter into reciprocity agreements
9 with foreign countries. The rules shall specify that the driver
10 license standards of the foreign country shall be comparable to
11 those of this state. The rules shall also require foreign drivers,
12 who are operating a motor vehicle in Oklahoma under such a
13 reciprocity agreement, to comply with the compulsory motor vehicle
14 liability insurance and financial responsibility laws of this state.
15 2. Service Oklahoma shall enter into a reciprocity agreement
16 for driver licenses with the country of Ireland.
17 E. When an automated driving system, as defined by Section 1701
18 of this title, installed on a motor vehicle is engaged, the
19 following shall apply:
20 1. The automated driving system is considered the driver or
21 operator, for the purpose of assessing compliance with applicable
22 traffic or motor vehicle laws, and shall be deemed to satisfy
23 electronically all physical acts required by a driver or operator of
24 the vehicle; and
